        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 7:35PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 735 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Roe, or near Clarendon, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dobbs Landing...                  Peppers Landing...
Aberdeen...                       Alfrey...
Louisiana Purchase State Park...  Monroe...
Roe...                            Blackton...
Clarendon...                      Palmer...
Pine City...                      Keevil...
Allendale...                      Holly Grove...
Duncan...                         Ulm...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 200 AM CDT for
eastern and southeastern Arkansas.</instruction>
